<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1291: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-17T13:00:00+08:00">September 17, 1930—1
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 17—10:50
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>820. Legation’s 765, August 29, 5 p.m. Following is translation of last
                            paragraph of note, dated September 15, from Ministry of Foreign Affairs:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“This Ministry has referred the above by telegraph to the Yunnan
                                    Provincial Government for consideration and action. A reply has
                                        <pb facs="0287" n="189" xml:id="pg_189"/> now been received
                                    stating that it has telegraphed the commanding generals on the
                                    fronts to make an investigation and to promptly return the
                                    lighters as well as to instruct the various units scrupulously
                                    to protect foreigners.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>